[227.55495, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       \u001b[1m[-+]O [\u001b[4m\u001b[22m\u001b[7mshopt\u001b[27m\u001b[1m\u001b[4m\u001b[22m_option\u001b[24m\u001b[1m]\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n                 \u001b[4m\u001b[7mshopt\u001b[27m\u001b[4m_option\u001b[24m  is  one of the shell options accepted by the\u001b[m\r\n                 \u001b[1m\u001b[7mshopt\u001b[27m\u001b[1m \u001b[22mbuiltin (see  \u001b[1mSHELL  BUILTIN  COMMANDS  \u001b[22mbelow).   If\u001b[m\r\n                 \u001b[4m\u001b[7mshopt\u001b[27m\u001b[4m_option\u001b[24m is present, \u001b[1m-O \u001b[22msets the value of that option;\u001b[m\r\n                 \u001b[1m+O  \u001b[22munsets it.  If \u001b[4m\u001b[7mshopt\u001b[27m\u001b[1m\u001b[22m\u001b[4m_option\u001b[24m is not supplied, the names\u001b[m\r\n                 and values of the shell  options  accepted  by  \u001b[1m\u001b[7mshopt\u001b[27m\u001b[1m  \u001b[22mare\u001b[m\r\n                 printed  on the standard output.  If the invocation option\u001b[m\r\n                 is \u001b[1m+O\u001b[22m, the output is displayed in a  format  that  may  be\u001b[m\r\n                 reused as input.\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m--        \u001b[22mA  \u001b[1m--  \u001b[22msignals the end of options and disables further op‐\u001b[m\r\n                 tion processing.  Any arguments after the \u001b[1m--  \u001b[22mare  treated\u001b"]
[227.55514, "o", "[m\r\n                 as  filenames  and arguments.  An argument of \u001b[1m- \u001b[22mis equiva‐\u001b[m\r\n                 lent to \u001b[1m--\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mBash \u001b[22malso interprets a number of multi-character options.  These op‐\u001b[m\r\n       tions must appear on the command line  before  the  single-character\u001b[m\r\n       options to be recognized.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m--debugger\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 52 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
